{
  "stem": "19550.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "But nothing is going to happen to them.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And if they have too much of a contact with them, maybe it will reflect upon them.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "So to persuade people to give money and food and, and dishes and clothing was a very difficult operation for the few able-bodied-- I, I should even say able-minded-- youngsters who are around.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And this went on for, for days.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "I really don't know exactly for how long, because the operation of bringing the Jews in from the neighboring villages was just-- seemed almost haphazard as, as far as the authorities were concerned.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "I'm sure it wasn't, but they just brought them in and plunked them down.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "There were no preparations of any kind that were made for them, so that it was up to the few people like myself to attempt to bring some order and to try to at least prevent these people who were brought in from dying of starvation, from dying of exposure, from dying of hunger.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "It, it was a, a, a hell of a mess.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "You know, the next transport that came in, we went to a, to a man by the name of [INAUDIBLE] who had-- on Star Street-- a big lumber yard.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And he had a huge open shed that only had a roof and no sides.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And incidentally, Mr.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE] was, I think, one of two Jews who remained in Kisvarda who was not deported, because he was, I think, an American citizen.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "There was one other man who was allowed to stay because he was 100% a war veteran, a war invalid from the First World War.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And so we brought the people in there.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
